ul.li:
Hyphenated compounds formed with RFC numbers should be avoided;
      this can be accomplished by: rewording the sentence (e.g., change "[RFC5011]-style
      rollover" to "rollover as described in RFC 5011").

section.t:
[STD72]   Gellens, R. and J. Klensin, "Message Submission
             for Mail", IETF, STD 72, RFC 6409, DOI 10.17487/RFC6409, November 2011,
             <https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/std72>.
